.SH NAME
Storage \- Storage
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Storage\f[B]\f[R] interface of the Web Storage API
provides access to a particular domain\(cqs session or local storage.
It allows, for example, the addition, modification, or deletion of
stored data items.
.PP
To manipulate, for instance, the session storage for a domain, a call to
\f[CR]Window.sessionStorage\f[R] is made; whereas for local storage the
call is made to \f[CR]Window.localStorage\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]Storage.length\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns an integer representing the number of data items stored in the
\f[CR]Storage\f[R] object.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]Storage.key()\f[R]
When passed a number \f[CR]n\f[R], this method will return the name of
the nth key in the storage.
.TP
\f[B]Storage.getItem()\f[R]
When passed a key name, will return that key\(cqs value.
.TP
\f[B]Storage.setItem()\f[R]
When passed a key name and value, will add that key to the storage, or
update that key\(cqs value if it already exists.
.TP
\f[B]Storage.removeItem()\f[R]
When passed a key name, will remove that key from the storage.
.TP
\f[B]Storage.clear()\f[R]
When invoked, will empty all keys out of the storage.
.SH EXAMPLES
Here we access a \f[CR]Storage\f[R] object by calling
\f[CR]localStorage\f[R].
We first test whether the local storage contains data items using
\f[CR]!localStorage.getItem(\(aqbgcolor\(aq)\f[R].
If it does, we run a function called \f[CR]setStyles()\f[R] that grabs
the data items using \f[CR]Storage.getItem()\f[R] and uses those values
to update page styles.
If it doesn\(cqt, we run another function, \f[CR]populateStorage()\f[R],
which uses \f[CR]Storage.setItem()\f[R] to set the item values, then
runs \f[CR]setStyles()\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[B]if\f[R] (!localStorage.getItem(\(dqbgcolor\(dq)) {
  populateStorage();
} \f[B]else\f[R] {
  setStyles();
}

\f[B]function\f[R] populateStorage() {
  localStorage.setItem(\(dqbgcolor\(dq, document.getElementById(\(dqbgcolor\(dq).value);
  localStorage.setItem(\(dqfont\(dq, document.getElementById(\(dqfont\(dq).value);
  localStorage.setItem(\(dqimage\(dq, document.getElementById(\(dqimage\(dq).value);

  setStyles();
}

\f[B]function\f[R] setStyles() {
  \f[B]const\f[R] currentColor = localStorage.getItem(\(dqbgcolor\(dq);
  \f[B]const\f[R] currentFont = localStorage.getItem(\(dqfont\(dq);
  \f[B]const\f[R] currentImage = localStorage.getItem(\(dqimage\(dq);

  document.getElementById(\(dqbgcolor\(dq).value = currentColor;
  document.getElementById(\(dqfont\(dq).value = currentFont;
  document.getElementById(\(dqimage\(dq).value = currentImage;

  htmlElem.style.backgroundColor = \(ga#${currentColor}\(ga;
  pElem.style.fontFamily = currentFont;
  imgElem.setAttribute(\(dqsrc\(dq, currentImage);
}
